5 DAY TRIPS from Toulouse, France 🇫🇷 #sponsored 

@airtransat is offering direct flights from Montréal to Toulouse! 😍 Save these epic day trips for your next adventures in France!

1. Adventure to la Passerelle de Mazamet. This suspended bridge is 70m above ground and 140m long. You can also choose to adventure the Via Ferrata! At the summit is a must-visit medieval village with incredible views! You’ll find restaurants and snack bars. It’s also possible to visit at night while the bridge is lit up. @tourismetarn 

2. Visit la Cité de Carcassonne. This unique place includes 52 towers, a castle, a fortress, a village and so much more! It’s an absolute must-visit for an unforgettable experience. @audetourisme 

3. Hike Roquefixade and admire the Château de Roquefixade Cathar castle. Our hike was moody with a lot of fog which really set the tone for this epic adventure! Maybe you’ll also come across goats like we did. 🐐 @tourismeariege 

4. Head to la Maison de Sidobre and get yourself a map! There are so many beautiful hiking trails to take. This one was called La Peyro Clabado which is a gigantic block of granite! @tourismetarn 

5. Treat yourself to a Spa day at the Château de Fiac! This stunning Hotel offers a swimming pool, a restaurant, terrace, and a garden. @tourismetarn 

Which one interests you the most out of these 5? 😍🫶🏼

@voyageoccitanie @explorefrance #ExperienceTransat #ExploreFrance #France #VoyageOccitanie #TourismeTarn #AudeTourisme #VisitezToulouse #TourismeAriege

This is your sign to book a life-changing experience! @airtransat is offering 5 direct weekly flights between MONTREAL and TOULOUSE all summer! 😍☀️ #Ad #ExperienceTransat 

I always fly with Air Transat for my trips! The flight is always so enjoyable and their touch screens make it super easy to watch your favorite movies or TV shows while sipping on your choice of beverage. ☕️🍷 You can even play some fun games such as solitaire or sudoku. I helped this cute little man sitting next to me win his first game of solitaire! It was such a core memory. We laughed as he rushed to finish it before landing. ❤️

I also booked with Option Plus because you receive priority check-in, first checked bag free of charge, seat selection, priority boarding, an exclusive check-in counter, and also special attention on board for optimal comfort. It’s honestly so worth it!

You absolutely need to visit Occitanie at least once in your life! It is such a dream. 🥹🇫🇷

This is your opportunity to pack your bags and visit France this summer! ☀️

This hike brings you to a ruined castle! 🤯🏔️ It was SO impressive. We even met goats along the way 🐐 @airtransat #Sponsored 

The Castle of Roquefixade is located in Ariège, in the Occitanie region of France and was built around the 100th century. It over looks the village of Roquefixade below. @tourismeariege

🏠 I stayed in the Gîte d’étape de Roquefixade (Bed & Breakfast) in the village of Roquefixade. The trailhead starts directly at this location.
🥾 There are so many different trails you can take! You can even choose to hike from Roquefixade all the way to Montségur. Montségur offers another incredible castle much bigger than Roquefixade!
🏔️ The duration of the hike to the Roquefixade castle is 3KM on average and is considered a relatively easy hike!

✈️ If you’re planning on hiking in the South of France this summer, Air Transat is offering direct flights from Montreal to Toulouse! 😍 This is your chance to pack your bags and plan your next hiking adventure!

SAGUENAY 4 DAY TRIP! 😍 Save this for your next trip to the region. #sponsored 

➖DAY 1: Stay at @go_imago for 2 nights and visit the Monts-Valin national park located minutes from Imago Village!
❤️ Recommendations: Hike le Mirador & Pic de a hutte for sunset.

➖DAY 2: Drive to the Saguenay Fjord national park, go sea-kayaking and stay at @go_imago.
❤️ Recommendations: watch Belugas at Halte de Béluga and go sea-kayaking for sunset in Sainte-Rose at @a.rosedesvents

➖DAY 3: Check-out of @go_imago and head to Lac St-Jean. Stay 2 nights @jaunehotel. Visit the beautiful waterfall in Val-Jalbert located at @villagevaljalbert historical village
❤️ Recommendations: Eat at @bistrolaboca located near the hotel for incredible food! Stop at local shops and the haltes located by the roads for epic views over Lac St-Jean.

➖DAY 4: Book sea-doo switch and camping with @go_imago for an unforgettable experience on Lac St-Jean. 
❤️ Recommendations: Pick up some food at the café located at @jaunehotel and lunch at @bistrolaboca.

Traditional Medicinals offers a range of delicious organic teas. Because they love nature just as much as we do, they’re committed to sustainability and ethical sourcing.

🌺 Hibiscus Tea Seltzers Recipe:
💦 8oz boiling water
🌿 Traditional Medicinals Hibiscus Tea
💙 16oz seltzer water and ice 🧊
🍓 Strawberries, raspberries or blueberries

1️⃣ Pour 8oz freshly boiled water over one tea bag. Cover and let steep until cool.
2️⃣ Squeeze the bag of excess tea and compost the tea bag.
3️⃣ Once cooled, add ice and top with seltzer and berries!

2 epic adventures you need to try in the Outaouais, Québec! 😍

1️⃣ Kayak on the turquoise green water of Lac Edja with Carpe Diem Aventures.

➖ Follow them here: @carpediemaventures

📍Located in the Vallée-de-la-Gatineau county in the town of Blue Sea. 

🌊 Carpe Diem Aventures offers unique micro chalets, suspended tents and camping. Perfect for couples, friends and families! 🏕️ 

🛶 You can canoe, kayak or even paddle board on Lac Edja located directly on their site. They also offer many different experiences such as bike rentals, descent of the Picanoc river, archery and many others!

2️⃣ Visit the Parc Régional du Mont Morissette for an adventurous hike and admire the breathtaking panoramic views from the top of the tower!

📍Located in the Vallée-de-la-Gatineau county in the town of Blue Sea.

🥾 The Mont Morissette Regional Park offers incredible hiking trails and is part of one of the 12 PERO trails.

🐶 The park is pet-friendly, offers free parking and is open year-round.

🌲 You’ll find an 18-metre-high observation tower offering panoramic views which was built next to an abandoned 1930s fire observation tower. You can choose to hike or drive directly to it!

What’s your favorite activity in the Outaouais region? 😍

#outaouais #outaouaisfun

Save these for your next adventures! 🫶🏼

1️⃣ Lac-Edja with @carpediemaventures. Kayak, paddle-board or canoe the crystal clear turquoise green water.

2️⃣ Visit the Parc des Chutes de Denholm to admire a beautiful waterfall and hike the trails for breathtaking views of the region.

4️⃣ Hike the Mont Cayamant hiking trails and admire the views from the top of the fire tower.

🏔️ The panoramic tower offers a suspended net at the top! 
⛄️ The path is open all year long.

5 AUTUMN ACTIVITIES NEAR AND AT LAÖ CABINES 🍂🍁🤎☕️ 

1️⃣ Ride the Gondola at Mont-Orford for breathtaking landscapes! The top of the mountain offers 5 different lookouts where you can admire the autumn foliage! Located only minutes from Laö Cabines. 

2️⃣ Hike one of the many trails in the Mont-Orford National Park. I highly recommend Pic de la Roche Fendue. The view of the fall colors is stunning from the top!

3️⃣ Go for an autumn nature walk directly at Laö Cabines! They offer 4km of beautiful trails. There’s also a short-hike nearby called La Rouche trail which offers a beautiful view of Lac La Rouche!

4️⃣ Spend time enjoying yourself in one of Laö Cabines spas! Relax for an evening in your hot tub surrounded by nature and admire the beautiful autumn colors. 

5️⃣ Grab a paddle-board or kayak included with your stay at Laö Cabines and spend some time on the lake located directly on site.
